author: rooneg
msg: Comment-only changes; follow-ups to earlier changes.
Patch by: Malcolm Rowe <malcolm-svn-dev@farside.org.uk>
* subversion/libsvn_client/repos_diff.c
(struct edit_baton): Remove reference to RA_LIB (removed in r12801).
(temp_file_plain_cleanup_handler, temp_file_child_cleanup_handler):
Fix grammar and clarify comments.
(temp_file_cleanup_register): Remove comment about ensuring lifetime of
PATH (PATH has been copied within POOL since r2436).

part of the svn_delta_editor_t interface, as it's not.

author: giovannibajo
msg: Two bugfixes in case of command line errors, and error message
improvements.
* contrib/client-side/svnmerge.py:
Update todo list.
(OptionParser._add_builtins): Add -V alias for --version.
(OptionParser._fancy_getopt): Remove dead code.
(OptionParser.parse): Fix bug when no command is specified.
(OptionParser.error): Improve error message for wrong options
without command.
(main): Improve error message when there is no copy-from
information. Fix variable name in internal assertion.
* contrib/client-side/svnmerge_test.py:
Add new command line coverage tests.

author: julianfoad
msg: Don't bother suppressing "unused parameter" warnings in a few places, because
we don't in most places and there is no neat way to do so in general in C.

* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_files.c (svn_wc_is_adm_dir):
